{
  "texts": [
    "Intrusion detection depends mostly on the Principal Component Analysis because it can minimize the numbers of independent variables in a network.",
    "In a network setting, data could be very high dimensional in such a way that there are many irrelevant or redundant features.",
    "This is particularly so, especially when working with big data or big sets of data or when working in an environment with limited resources of time.",
    "Intrusion detection models benefit from data simplification since it allows them to run more quickly and with less computational cost.",
    "Federated learning is a novel approach that improves the state of collaborative intrusion detection without compromising the safety of confidential information."
  ]
}